**B2B Segmentation Exercise 1**

Exercise 1 - Create a segment for all contacts who have a position of &quot;VP&quot; who work at account &quot;Yacero&quot; and have visited the products webpage in the past 10 days.

1. Navigate to Segment Builder in the left navigation

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_1e498c3050c2333b.png)

1. Click &#39;Create segment&#39; on the top right.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_423c50e21a4980c7.png)

1. Click the gear icon to the right of Fields in the left pane

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_407e621cdc7e1f71.png)

1. Verify &#39;Show full XDM schema&#39; is selected, and if not, select it. Click on the gear icon again to hide the setting.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_a95852ae7a651daf.png)

1. Select &#39;Attributes&#39; under Fields

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_294240795d95fe95.png)

1. Click on &#39;XDM Individual Profile&#39; under Browse Classes

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_b5cf9312c46c12ef.png)

1. Click on &#39;Some Additional Person Work Details&#39;

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_7ee4ee92d24c1a21.png)

1. Drag the &#39;Job Title&#39; field over to the Segment canvas

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_e55ceb41bfdbc63a.png)

1. In the text box to the right of &#39;equals&#39;, type &quot;VP&quot; and press Enter to add the value to the list.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_bf9ccc76697f8dcc.png)

1. In the left pane, click &#39;XDM Individual Profile&#39; to navigate back to the top level of the class.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_ba3423eb59897b64.png)

1. Now, drill down into the folder structure to get to Account level details by selecting &#39;Person Components \&gt; Source Account Key \&gt; Account&#39;.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_5f07e6e326e65ae8.png)

1. Drag the &#39;Account Name&#39; field over to the Attributes section of the canvas, where it says &#39;Add attribute or audience&#39;.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_d73d17108362f20e.png)

1. In the text box to the right of &#39;equals&#39;, type &quot;Yacero&quot; and press Enter to add the value to the list.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_5fa04e63b9389361.png)

1. In the left pane, click &#39;Events&#39; under Fields.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_6509e0e7f696aa3c.png)

1. Click &#39;XDM Experience Event&#39; under Browse Classes

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_4ec31376b225ab99.png)

1. Drill down into the folder structure to get to Web Details by selecting &#39;Web \&gt; Web Page Details&#39;.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_d9955209ba904b9c.png)

1. Drag the &#39;URL&#39; field over to the Events section of the canvas.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_9a22fafdc0b17ad3.png)

1. In the text box to the right of equals, type &quot;yacero.com/products&quot; and hit Enter.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_f4dcbce8ee189958.png)

1. At the top of the &#39;Events&#39; canvas, update the time value to &#39;In Last 7 Days&#39;

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_df483bbb25992b0a.png)

1. Enter the segment name &quot;VP Product Page Viewers at Yacero&quot; followed by your lab attendee number. (Ex â€“ &quot;VP Product Page Viewers at Yacero 014&quot;).

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_b6e3d05a006c3362.png)

1. Click &#39;Save&#39; in the top right to save the segment.

![](RackMultipart20211105-4-r9h6k3_html_f3029a3705834d08.png)

